Defending champion  Rafael Nadal 
advanced to the third round of the U.S. Open when Nicolas Mahut
of  France  quit their match after losing the first two sets.  Nadal, the second seed from  Spain , was leading 6-2, 6-2
when Mahut retired 1 hour and 21 minutes into the match.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
